title: Mapmaking with free tools and public data
description: Huge roundup of mapping resources, starter instructions, and inspiration. I took an online GIS course back in the day but never did anything with it. I had other people export .eps files and beautified them in Illustrator. It could be fun to try some mapmaking from start to finish.

title: My Reading Philosophy and 17 Reading Guidelines
description: I read a lot, and have many opinions about how and what I want to read. These guidelines reflect my current reading philosophy. I expect everyone has their own opinions about reading, so though my wording is authoritative, I’m speaking to myself here 😉 Read according to whim. Read what I’m in the mood for, […]
